<LP>
   ICN BIOMEDICALS Inc. declared a special one-time dividend
of 3.5 cents a share. The special dividend is in addition to
the quarterly dividend of 3.5 cents a share. Both are payable
Nov. 1 to stock of record Oct. 16. ICN Biomedicals, a
supplier to the biotechnology research and clinical
diagnostic marketplaces said it declared the special dividend
"to recognize the continued growth and strong performance of
the company." The Costa Mesa, Calif., company has 11.3
million common shares outstanding. For the first half, the
company had net income of $4.7 million, or 42 cents a share,
on sales of $68.3 million, compared with net income of $2.5
million, or 23 cents a share, on sales of $27.1 million a
year earlier.
