<LP>
   The late English strategist Basil Liddell-Hart discussing
the end of the first world war in "The Real War," (Little
Brown, 1930):
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   {T}he much-abused Napoleonic saying that God is on the
side of the big battalions received yet another historical
contradiction from the Alexandrine principle of quality over
quantity. Once again the blend of superior hitting power with
superior mobility played havoc with an army which pinned its
faith to weight of human bodies.
</TEXT>
