   PEQUANNOCK, N.J. -- Eastern Shore Consolidated Industries
Inc. said it extended its tender offer to buy 586,000 shares
of MHP Machines Inc. common stock at 50 cents a share until
Oct. 9. The previous offer was to expire today. As of noon
yesterday, 92,500 shares had been tendered.
   MHP Machines of Cheektowaga, N.Y., makes computer
controlled metal-cutting machining and turning centers.
Eastern Shore Consolidated Industries was formed in July to
make the offer.
