<LP>
   PAPERS: Ad revenue of Times Mirror Co.'s newspaper
publishing group rose less than 1% in the four weeks ended
Sept. 2, to $121.7 million from $120.8 million for the
corresponding period a year earlier. For the first 35 weeks
of the year, ad revenue fell less than 1% to $1.11 billion
from $1.12 billion. The cumulative results this year included
35 Sundays vs. 36 a year ago.
                                                                                                       

</LP>
<TEXT>
   WHO'S NEWS: Marshall Turner was elected chairman and
Daniel Brenner was re-elected vice chairman of the board at
the Corporation for Public Broadcasting. Mr. Turner is a
general partner at Taylor &amp; Turner Associates Ltd. in San
Francisco. Mr. Brenner is counsel to LeBoeuf, Lamb, Lieby &amp;
MacRae in Los Angeles.
