<HL>
   Business Brief -- Ford Motor Co.:
   Auto Company Is Recalling
   Vans for Seat-Latch Work
</HL>
<DATE>
09/26/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   F
</CO>
<IN>
AUTOMOBILES (AUT)
</IN>
<LP>
   Ford Motor Co., Dearborn, Mich., said it is recalling
approximately 14,500 of its 1989-90 Aerostar minivans
equipped with "Quad" captain's chairs to replace latch
assemblies in the second-row, right-hand bucket seat. The
company said it is concerned that these seats, which are
designed to tilt forward to permit access to third-row seats,
may unlatch during severe frontal impacts. However, the
company said it is unaware of any accident in which the seat
has unlatched.
   In a second action, Ford is notifying owners of a
voluntary safety recall of approximately 18,000 of its
1989-90 L-Series heavy trucks to replace an air-brake check
valve that may malfunction and not close as intended. Ford
said it was unaware of any accidents stemming from this valve
malfunctioning.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Owners will be asked by mail to return the vehicles to
local dealers to have the work performed at no charge.
</TEXT>
